get%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20American%20teens%20are%20less%20likely%20than%20previous%20generations%20to%20take%20part%20in%20so-called%20%26quot%3Badult%26quot%3B%20activities%2C%20like%20being%20employed%2C%20drinking%20alcohol%2C%20and%20dating.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20data%20was%20echoed%20by%20findings%20from%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.americansurveycenter.org%2Fresearch%2Fgeneration-z-and-the-transformation-of-american-adolescence-how-gen-zs-formative-experiences-shape-its-politics-priorities-and-future%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESurvey%20Center%20on%20American%20Life%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20reported%20only%2056%25%20of%20Gen%20Z%20adults%20(the%20generation%20that%20my%20son%20belongs%20to)%20said%20they%20had%20any%20kind%20of%20romantic%20relationship%20in%20their%20teens%2C%20a%20drop%20from%2069%25%20of%20millennials%2C%2076%25%20of%20Gen%20X%2C%20and%2078%25%20of%20baby%20boomers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20reason%20I%20was%20surprised%20to%20find%20teens%20aren't%20dating%20as%20much%20is%20that%20my%20son%20and%20his%20friends%20have%20been%20talking%20about%20being%20in%20relationships%20for%20years%20%E2%80%94%20well%20before%20they%20were%20actually%20ready%20to%20do%20so%20%E2%80%94%20and%20I%20just%20assumed%20all%20teens%20were%20the%20same%20way.%20Since%20most%20of%20his%20friends%20have%20also%20begun%20relationships%20or%20already%20had%20their%20first%20break-up%2C%20it%20seems%20they%20also%20have%20a%20pretty%20laid-back%20approach%20to%20how%20long%20a%20relationship%20should%20last%20at%20this%20stage%20in%20their%20lives%2C%20which%20makes%20that%20fervor%20from%20long%20ago%20pretty%20funny%20to%20look%20back%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhatever%20does%20or%20doesn't%20happen%20with%20my%20son's%20relationship%2C%20it's%20fun%20to%20go%20on%20the%20ride%20with%20him%2C%20largely%20as%20an%20observer%2C%20and%20to%20witness%20him%20beginning%20to%20step%20into%20a%20safe%20version%20of%20adulth